				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Do people in other classes actually know how bards solo?<a name="33266"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 6 04 10:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Last night I was playing my alt berserker and I got into a conversation with an enchanter whose main is a druid.  We began discussing solo techniques and I mentioned that I really didn't much care for AoE kiting with my bard.  He wanted to know how a bard can do that and I described kiting snowcougar in Iceclad.  He didn't say anything for several minutes then asked how many cougars my DoTs were hitting if I had the entire island chasing me and I say &quot;All of them&quot;  More silence and then,  &quot;That's just not right..&quot;  He really freaked when I described swarm kiting,  apparently there's no way for a druid to do anything similar solo.  I have to wonder,  does SOE even know?  There are a number of things in the game that should be common knowledge that don't seem to be well known.  Are bard soloing techniques a sort of open secret?</span></td>
